    "what_description": "Petunia patagonica is a species of flowering plant in the family Solanaceae. It is an annual herb native to South America, characterized by a prostrate or decumbent growth habit and hairy stems and leaves. The leaves are elliptical to ovate in shape, measuring 2-4 cm in length, and have a cuneate base and a pointed apex. The flowers are trumpet-shaped, measuring 2-3 cm in length, and have a purple to pink color with a white or yellow throat. The flowers are arranged in a terminal, pedunculate inflorescence, and are produced from mid-spring to early summer.",
