    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Petunia patagonica are patagonic tincture, petunia tea, patagonic tea, patagonic salve, and infused oil. Patagonic tincture is a concentrated liquid extract of the plant's aerial parts, typically made using ethanol or glycerin as a solvent, and is used to treat various health issues, including anxiety and insomnia. Petunia tea is a decoction of the plant's leaves and flowers, traditionally used to calm the nervous system and promote relaxation, while patagonic tea is a specific preparation of the plant's aerial parts, used to treat digestive issues. Patagonic salve is a topical cream or ointment made from the plant's aerial parts, used to treat skin conditions such as wounds and inflammation. Infused oil is a liquid extract of the plant's aerial parts in a carrier oil, typically used to treat skin conditions and promote wound healing.",
